SHARED FACILITIES AND USE AGREEMENT
This SHARED FACILITIES AND USE AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”), dated as
of May 23, 2023, is between Earthrise Shelby County Interconnection, LLC, (“Interconnection
Company”), and Shelby County Energy Center, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company
(“Generator”). Interconnection Company and Generator are sometimes referred to herein
individually as a “Party”, and collectively as the “Parties”.
RECITALS
A. Generator owns and operates a thermal energy generation facility located in Neoga,
Illinois (the “Project”).
B. Transmission Owner owns or operates the Transmission System (defined below),
whose operations are subject to the functional control of the Transmission Provider (defined
below), to which the Project is interconnected.
C. Generator and Ameren Services Company as agent for Union Electric Company
and Central Illinois Public Service Company (“Transmission Owner”) have entered into that
certain Transmission System Interconnection Agreement dated as of April 28, 2000 (as amended,
amended and restated or otherwise supplemented from time to time, the “LGIA”), for purposes of
establishing the parties’ rights and obligations related to the interconnection and operation of the
Project with the Transmission System, including Generator’s entitlement to the Interconnection
Rights (defined below).
D. Generator and Interconnection Company have entered into that certain Purchase
and Sale Agreement, dated as of May 23, 2023 (“PSA”), pursuant to which Generator transferred
to Interconnection Company (i) certain assets, contracts (including the LGIA), personal property,
fixtures, equipment and/or facilities owed by Generator and associated with the Project and the
Interconnection Rights, which property, fixtures, equipment and facilities are further described in
Exhibit A attached hereto (the “Common Facilities”) and (ii) the rights to the real property under
and immediately adjacent to the Common Facilities that is necessary for the operation and
maintenance of the Common Facilities, which area is further described in Exhibit B attached hereto
(the “Common Facilities Area”), subject to and on the terms and conditions specified therein.
F. Interconnection Company and Generator are entering into this Agreement to
establish their respective rights and obligations with respect to the Common Facilities, the
Common Facilities Area and the Interconnection Rights.
AGREEMENT
In consideration of the mutual covenants contained herein and for other good and valuable
consideration, the receipt, adequacy and legal sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, and
intending to be legally bound the Parties agree as follows:
ARTICLE I
DEFINITIONS; RULES OF INTERPRETATION
2
Section 1.1 Definitions. Unless otherwise required by the context in which any
capitalized term appears, initially capitalized terms used in this Agreement shall have the
following meanings:
“Additional Agreements” has the meaning set forth in Section 2.2(a).
“Additional Generators” has the meaning set forth in Section 2.2(a).
“Additional Project” means any energy generating project and/or energy storage project
owned by an Additional Generator and subject to an Additional Agreement between
Interconnection Company and such Additional Generator.
“Adverse Event” has the meaning set forth in Section 6.2(a).
“AE Costs” has the meaning set forth in Section 6.2(b).
“Affected Party” has the meaning set forth in the definition of Force Majeure.
“Affiliate” means, with respect to any designated Person, each Person that directly or
indirectly controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with, such designated Person,
with “control” meaning the possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct management
and policies, whether through the ownership of voting securities or by contract or otherwise.
“Agreement” has the meaning set forth in the Preamble to this Agreement.
“Assign” and “Assignment” has the meaning set forth in Section 12.1(a).
“Assigning Party” has the meaning set forth in Section 12.1(b).
“Business Day” means every day other than a Saturday, Sunday or day which is a legal
holiday in New York, New York on which banks are not generally open for business.
“Common Facilities” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals to this Agreement.
“Common Facilities Area” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals to this Agreement.
“Common Facilities O&M Agreement” has the meaning set forth in Section 4.1(a).
“Condemnation” has the meaning set forth in Section 10.4.
“Condemnation Date” has the meaning set forth in Section 10.4.
“Condemnation Notice” has the meaning set forth in Section 10.4.
“Coordinated Interconnection Rights” has the meaning set forth in Section 2.1.
“Defaulting Party” has the meaning set forth in Section 8.4.
“Effective Date” has the meaning set forth in Section 8.2.
3
“Electricity Products and Services” means, with respect to the Project or an Additional
Project, all electricity and related products and services produced or made available by the Project
or Additional Project, as the case may be, including capacity, energy, ancillary services and any
related financial or non-physical attributes associated with any of the foregoing.
“Environmental Law” means any applicable Law that relates to pollution, occupational
safety, protection of occupational health or the protection of the environment.
“Event of Default” has the meaning set forth in Section 8.4.
“FERC” means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
“Financing” has the meaning set forth in Section 12.1(c).
“Force Majeure” or an “event of Force Majeure” means an event or circumstance that
prevents a Party (the “Affected Party”) from performing, in whole or in part, an obligation under
this Agreement and that is not within the reasonable control of or the result of the negligence or
fault of the Affected Party, and that could not be overcome or its effects mitigated by the use of
due diligence by the Affected Party. Force Majeure includes the following types of events and
circumstances (but only to the extent that such events or circumstances satisfy the requirements in
the preceding sentence): tornado, hurricane, lightning, tsunami, flood, earthquake and other acts
of God; fire; explosion; invasion, acts of terrorism, war (declared or undeclared) or other armed
conflict; riot, revolution, insurrection or similar civil disturbance; epidemic or global pandemic;
sabotage; strikes, walkouts, lock-outs, work stoppages or other labor disputes; and action or
restraint by Governmental Authority; provided, that the Affected Party has not applied for or
assisted in the application for, and has opposed to the extent commercially reasonable, such action
or restraint.
“Generator” has the meanings set forth in the Preamble to this Agreement.
“Governmental Approvals” means registrations, permits, licenses, authorizations,
consents, approvals, grants, franchises, variances, certificates of authority, letter rulings, or similar
rights and privileges granted by or obtained from any Governmental Authority.
“Governmental Authorities” means any federal, state, local, or other governmental,
regulatory or administrative agency, court, commission, department, board, or other governmental
subdivision, legislature, rulemaking board, tribunal, or other governmental authority, including
FERC, NERC, SERC, and any applicable regional reliability entity, any balancing authority
(including Transmission Provider), and any other transmission provider, in each case, having
jurisdiction over the Person (or its property or operations) or matter at issue.
“Hazardous Substance” means: (a) any petroleum or petroleum products, flammable
materials, explosives, radioactive materials, friable asbestos, urea formaldehyde foam insulation
and transformers or other equipment that contain dielectric fluid containing polychlorinated
biphenyls (PCBs) in regulated concentrations; (b) any chemicals or other materials or substances
which are now or hereafter become defined as or included in the definition of “hazardous
substances,” “hazardous wastes,” “hazardous materials,” “extremely hazardous wastes,”
“restricted hazardous wastes,” “toxic substances,” “toxic pollutants,” “contaminants,” “pollutants”
4
or words of similar import under any Environmental Law; and (c) any other chemical or other
material or substance, exposure to which is now or hereafter prohibited, limited or regulated as
such under any Environmental Law.
“Indemnified Party” has the meaning set forth in Section 9.1.
“Indemnifying Party” has the meaning set forth in Section 9.1.
“Interconnection Company” has the meaning set forth in the Preamble to this Agreement.
“Interconnection Company Indemnified Party” has the meaning set forth in Section 9.2.
“Interconnection Rights” means the interconnection service provided pursuant to the
LGIA.
“Interference” and “Interfere” means a materially adverse impact on (a) the use of or access
to the Common Facilities or the Common Facilities Area or the Interconnection Rights (consistent
with the LGIA) by any Party or (b) the operation and maintenance of the Common Facilities or
the Common Facilities Area or the performance under the LGIA, in each case, as provided for by
this Agreement.
“Landowner” has the meaning set forth in Section 3.5.
“Laws” means any federal, state, local or other law, treaty, code, rule, regulation,
ordinance, permit, certificate, authorization, approval or binding directive, order, order, writ,
judgment, injunction, decree, ruling, stipulation, determination or award of a Governmental
Authority, including the common law, any Environmental Law, any FERC rule or regulation, any
Transmission Provider Rules (or any tariff, rule, requirement, policy, protocol or procedure of any
other applicable balancing authority), and any NERC or other applicable regional reliability entity
requirement, including any NERC reliability standard, which is binding on the Project or
Additional Project or Person (or its property or operations) at issue.
“Lender” has the meaning set forth in Section 12.1(c).
“LGIA” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals of this Agreement.
“Lien” means, with respect to any property of any Person, any mortgage, lien, deed of trust,
hypothecation, fiduciary transfer of title, assignment by way of security, lien, pledge, charge, lease,
sale and lease-back arrangement, easement, servitude, trust arrangement, or security interest or
encumbrance of any kind in respect of such property, or any preferential arrangement having the
practical effect of constituting a security interest with respect to the payment of any obligation
with, or from the proceeds of, any property of any kind (and a Person shall be deemed to own
subject to a Lien any property that it has acquired or holds subject to the interest of a vendor or
lessor under any conditional sale agreement, capital lease or other title retention agreement relating
to such property).
“Losses” has the meaning set forth in Section 9.1.
5
“MW” means megawatt of energy produced by the Project.
“Notice” and “Notices” has the meaning set forth in Section 13.1.
“NERC” means the North American Electric Reliability Corporation.
“Operator” has the meaning set forth in Section 4.1(a).
“Party” and “Parties” have the meanings set forth in the Preamble to this Agreement.
“Person” means any natural person, partnership, limited liability company, joint venture,
corporation, trust, unincorporated organization, or Governmental Authority.
“Pro Rata Share” means, with respect to the Project and Generator or an Additional Project
and Additional Generator, a proportionate share of any Shared Expenses, resource, cost or other
item to be allocated to the Common Facilities or Common Facilities Area under or in connection
with this Agreement that, as of any date of determination, shall be equal to a fraction, the numerator
of which shall be the aggregate nameplate capacity of the Project or Additional Project, as the case
may be, and the denominator of which shall be the aggregate nameplate capacity of the Project
and all Additional Projects, which for the purposes of determining the Pro Rata Share for Generator
and any Additional Generators shall include any energy generating and/or storage facilities
installed, commissioned and using the Common Facilities and Common Facilities Area. Pro Rata
Shares shall be calculated to at least two decimal places and shall be rounded upward, to the extent
necessary, so that the sum of the Pro Rata Share of the Project Owners shall be equal to one
hundred percent (100%); provided, however, until Interconnection Company negotiates an
Additional Agreement with an Additional Generator, Generator’s Pro Rata Share shall be equal to
one hundred percent (100%).
“Project” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals to this Agreement.
“Project Owners” means Generator and any Additional Generator.
“Prudent Operating Practice” means any of the practices, methods and acts engaged in or
approved by a significant portion of the electric power generation and transmission industry for
facilities of similar size, characteristics and geographical region, or any of the practices, methods
or acts, which, in the exercise of reasonable judgment in the light of the facts known at the time a
decision is made, would reasonably have been expected to accomplish the desired result at the
lowest reasonable cost consistent with reliability, safety and expedition. Prudent Operating
Practices is not intended to be limited to the optimum practice, method or act, to the exclusion of
all others, but rather is intended to include acceptable practices, methods and acts generally
accepted in the electric power generation and transmission industry for facilities of similar size,
characteristics and geographical region.
“SERC” means the SERC Reliability Corporation.
“Shared Expenses” means certain common costs and expenses reasonably necessary for
the operation and maintenance of the Common Facilities and Common Facilities Area, including
the following:
6
(a) the operating costs associated with and other significant expenses necessary
for the operation of the Common Facilities, which operating costs may include road maintenance,
weed abatement, equipment repairs, snow removal and employee training;
(b) the costs of any capital improvements necessary to maintain or operate the
Common Facilities in accordance with applicable Law or Prudent Operating Practice, including in
any manner required under any Common Facilities O&M Agreement, which costs shall be
amortized over the useful life of the improvement by Interconnection Company in accordance with
sound accounting and management principles consistently applied;
(c) costs associated with scheduled and unscheduled maintenance, including
any parts or supplies, heavy equipment, rentals, third party engineering, maintenance or consulting
services required by Interconnection Company in order to maintain the Common Facilities in good
working order;
(d) insurance covering the Common Facilities and the Common Facilities Area
under any blanket policy providing casualty and liability insurance where each Party is a named
or additional insured;
(e) property and other use or ad valorem taxes assessed against or allocated to
the Common Facilities and/or the Common Facilities Area;
(f) reasonable operation fees payable to the Operator, if any, under the
Common Facilities O&M Agreement, provided, that such operation and maintenance fees relate
only to such Operator’s operation and maintenance of the Common Facilities and the Common
Facilities Area;
(g) the amount of any fees, rents or other similar payments paid to any
Landowners in respect of the Common Facilities Area;
(h) costs that Interconnection Company is responsible for under the LGIA, and
any costs related to the Interconnection Rights; and
(i) costs and expenses incurred by or on behalf of Interconnection Company to
administer the Coordinated Interconnection Rights for the benefit of Generator and any Additional
Generator which are not directly caused by Generator or any Additional Generator.
Notwithstanding anything to the contrary herein, the term Shared Expenses shall not
include: (i) costs of capital improvements, except as provided for in clause (b) above; (ii)
depreciation and amortization of the Common Facilities or financing costs, including interest and
principal amortization of debts; (iii) damages incurred due to default by Interconnection Company
under the terms of any Site Agreement; (iv) costs, fines or penalties incurred due to the violation
by Interconnection Company of any Law; (v) any expenditures for which Interconnection
Company has been reimbursed or is entitled to reimbursement from any Person who has failed to
pay or reimburse the same when due; (vi) any amount incurred by Interconnection Company by
reason of Interconnection Company’s gross negligence or willful misconduct; (vii) any costs
included in Shared Expenses representing an amount paid to an Affiliate of Interconnection
Company in excess of the amount which would have been paid on a fair market value basis in the
7
absence of such Affiliate relationship; (viii) the initial costs of equipment properly chargeable to
a capital account using generally accepted accounting principles consistently applied or the
original costs of constructing the Common Facilities; (ix) costs to correct original or latent defects
in the design, construction or equipment of the Common Facilities to the extent such costs are
recoverable from the applicable contractor or supplier; (x) any repair, rebuilding or other work
necessitated by Condemnation, fire, windstorm or other insured casualty or hazard except to the
extent such work is not covered by the insurance required to be carried by Interconnection
Company hereunder; or (xi) those expenses to be paid in accordance with Section 6.2(b).
“Site Agreement” and “Site Agreements” have the meanings set forth in Section 3.5.
“Surplus Interconnection Service Generator Interconnection Agreements” have the
meaning set forth in Section 2.2(a).
“Transmission Owner” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals to this Agreement.
“Transmission Provider” means the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc.
“Transmission Provider Rules” means, collectively, (a) the Transmission Provider Tariff,
(b) the Transmission Provider Business Practice Manuals (as defined in the Transmission Provider
Tariff) and (c) all other applicable binding policies, rules, guidelines, procedures, protocols,
standards, criteria, instructions, directives, and requirements of Transmission Provider.
“Transmission Provider Tariff” means the Transmission Provider Open Access
Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Market Tariff on file with FERC.
Section 1.2 Rules of Interpretation.
(a) Rules of Interpretation. Unless otherwise required by the context in which
any term appears: (i) the singular includes the plural and vice versa; (ii) references to “Articles,”
“Sections” or “Exhibits” are to articles or sections of or exhibits to this Agreement; (iii) all
references to a particular entity include a reference to such entity’s successors and permitted
assigns; (iv) “herein,” “hereof” and “hereunder” refer to this Agreement as a whole; (v) the
masculine includes the feminine and neuter and vice versa; (vi) “including,” “includes,” and
“included” mean “including, without limitation” or “including, but not limited to”; (vii) all
references to a particular Law mean that Law as amended, modified, supplemented or superseded
from time to time and includes all rules and regulations promulgated thereunder; (viii) the word
“or” is not necessarily exclusive; (ix) reference to “days,” “months” and “years” means calendar
days, months and years, respectively, unless expressly stated otherwise in this Agreement; and (x)
any items required to be delivered on a “day” that is not a Business Day shall be required to be
delivered on the next Business Day.
(b) Terms Not to be Construed For or Against Either Party. Each term in this
Agreement must be construed according to its fair meaning and not strictly for or against either
Party. In the event an ambiguity or question of intent or interpretation arises with respect to this
Agreement, this Agreement shall be construed as if drafted jointly by the Parties and no
presumption or burden of proof shall arise favoring or disfavoring any Party by virtue of authorship
of any of the provisions of this Agreement.
8
(c) Headings. The headings used for the Articles and Sections of this
Agreement are for convenience and reference purposes only and in no way affect the meaning or
interpretation of the provisions of this Agreement.
ARTICLE II
COORDINATED INTERCONNECTION RIGHTS
Section 2.1 Nature of Coordinated Interconnection Rights. Interconnection Company
shall make available to Generator during the term of this Agreement the Interconnection Rights
to allow all Electricity Products and Services from the Project to reach the Transmission System
in accordance with the terms of the LGIA and this Agreement (collectively, the “Coordinated
Interconnection Rights”). The Coordinated Interconnection Rights provided by Interconnection
Company to Generator shall not relieve Interconnection Company of its obligations under the
LGIA.
Section 2.2 Additional Generators; Additional Agreements; Adjustment to Pro Rata
Share.
(a) The Parties recognize that Generator may enter into one or more agreements
with Transmission Provider and one or more Affiliates of the Generator to provide interconnection
service to one or more Affiliates of the Generator over any portion of the interconnection service
provided to the Generator under the LGIA provided that such agreements shall provide Generator
continued access to the interconnection service to permit Generator to continue Generator’s
performance of its obligations to sell and deliver capacity and energy from the Project (“Surplus
Interconnection Service Generator Interconnection Agreements”).
(b) The Parties recognize that Interconnection Company may subsequently
enter into one or more shared facilities and use agreements with other owners of energy generating
projects and/or energy storage projects (“Additional Generators”) who will utilize all or a portion
of the Common Facilities, the Common Facilities Area and/or the Interconnection Rights provided
that such agreements shall provide Generator continued access to Common Facilities, Common
Facilities Areas and Interconnection Rights to permit Generator to continue Generator’s
performance of its obligations to sell and deliver capacity and energy from the Project (“Additional
Agreements”).
(c) Subject to Section 2.5, Interconnection Company shall not, in the exercise
of its obligations under this Agreement, discriminate against the Project or Generator in favor of
any Additional Project or Additional Generator.
(d) If Interconnection Company allows the additional use of the Common
Facilities, the Common Facilities Area and/or the Interconnection Rights in accordance with the
terms of Section 2.2, then Generator’s Pro Rata Share shall be adjusted accordingly.
Section 2.3 Obligations of Interconnection Company. Interconnection Company shall
exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is consistent
with its obligations under the LGIA and that will allow all Electricity Products and Services from
the Project to reach the Transmission System in accordance with the terms of the LGIA and this
9
Agreement. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement,
Interconnection Company shall:
(a) Perform its obligations under this Agreement and the LGIA in a manner
consistent with the terms of the LGIA;
(b) Comply with all provisions of the LGIA to which it is subject;
(c) Promptly provide to Generator any notices it receives under the LGIA from
Transmission Provider or Transmission Owner;
(d) Not amend, restate, assign or terminate the LGIA, without Generator’s prior
written consent, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and in each
case, subject to receipt of any Governmental Approvals required by applicable Law; and
(e) Cause the Common Facilities to be operated and maintained in accordance
with the LGIA and this Agreement.
Section 2.4 Obligations of Generator. Generator shall exercise its rights and perform
its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is reasonable and facilitates Interconnection
Company’s performance under and compliance with the LGIA and this Agreement. Without
limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, Generator shall:
(a) Operate the Project in a manner consistent with the terms of the LGIA;
(b) Facilitate and cause Interconnection Company’s compliance with all
provisions of the LGIA to which Interconnection Company is subject as it relates to the Project;
(c) Not take, or fail to take, any action which would result in a breach of or
default under the LGIA by Interconnection Company;
(d) Use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical
issues arising in connection with the operation of the Project that might reasonably be expected to
result in a breach of or default under the LGIA, and if such breach or default occurs, to promptly
assist Interconnection Company to cure such breach or default in accordance with the terms of the
LGIA;
(e) Provide Interconnection Company with all reasonable information
regarding the operation, maintenance and condition of the Project as Interconnection Company
may request to facilitate compliance with the terms and conditions of the LGIA; and
(f) Provide to Interconnection Company copies of all notices and instructions
received by it that affect Interconnection Company’s rights and obligations and performance under
the LGIA.
Section 2.5 Access to Interconnection Rights. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary
contained in this Agreement, in the event of an emergency action taken by the Transmission
Provider or Transmission Owner pursuant to the LGIA (or pursuant to applicable operating guides
or applicable reliability standards and requirements), unless otherwise required by the
10
Transmission Provider or Transmission Owner, the Parties agree that the Project and any
Additional Project, as applicable, shall have access to Interconnection Rights (to the extent any
Additional Project has access to the Interconnection Rights pursuant to an Additional Agreement)
pursuant to the direction and operating guidelines of the Transmission Provider as follows:
(a) first, to the Project;
(b) second, in all other circumstances (other than as set forth in Section 2.5(c))
below, to any Additional Project or pro rata to any Additional Projects, as applicable; and
(c) third and last, to the extent Transmission Owner or Transmission Provider
has specifically identified such emergency as arising solely as a result of the Project or an
Additional Project, to the Project or Additional Project, as applicable.
Section 2.6 No Joint and Several Liability with Additional Generators. The Parties
acknowledge and agree that this Agreement does not subject Generator to joint and several or
other liability of any kind for any actions taken or not taken by any Additional Generator pursuant
to or in connection with any Additional Agreement, including if such actions taken or not taken
by such Additional Generator cause the Interconnection Company to be in breach or default under
the LGIA.
ARTICLE III
COMMON FACILITIES AND COMMON FACILITIES AREA
Section 3.1 Non-Exclusive License to the Common Facilities.
(a) The Parties hereby declare that their relationship in and to the Common
Facilities (but excluding the Common Facilities Area, which relationship of the Parties shall be
governed by Section 3.2) is and will be that of owner and licensee, expressly subject to the terms,
conditions, limitations and requirements set forth in this Agreement. Nothing contained in this
Agreement will be deemed to constitute the Parties as partners or joint venturers.
(b) Subject to the terms and conditions contained herein, Interconnection
Company hereby grants to Generator during the term of this Agreement an irrevocable nonexclusive right to use the Common Facilities as a licensee, to the extent reasonably necessary, for
the purpose of the operation and maintenance of the Project. The license granted herein is and
shall be a license coupled with an interest and shall be and is intended to be (i) irrevocable (subject
to the provisions of Section 8.3) and (ii) binding on successors and permitted assigns of
Interconnection Company.
Section 3.2 Easement Rights and Access to the Common Facilities Area.
(a) The Parties hereby declare that their relationship in and to the Common
Facilities Area is and will be that of grantor and grantee, expressly subject to the terms, conditions,
limitations and requirements set forth in this Agreement. Nothing contained in this Agreement
will be deemed to constitute the Parties as partners or joint venturers.
11
(b) Subject to the terms and conditions contained herein, Interconnection
Company hereby grants to Generator during the term of this Agreement a non-exclusive and

collectively, the “Lenders”). Such notice shall include the names of the agents or other

12.1(c), the following provisions shall apply:
(i) The Parties, except as provided by the terms of this Agreement, shall

opportunity to prevent or cure any breach or Event of Default within a reasonable additional time
period. The Lenders or their designees shall have the right, but not the obligation, to perform any
act required to be performed by Generator under this Agreement to prevent or cure any breach or
Event of Default by Generator within the time period granted to Generator herein, and such act
performed by the Lenders or their designees shall be as effective to prevent or cure a breach or
Event of Default as if done by Generator;

execute statements certifying that this Agreement is unmodified (or, modified and stating the
nature of the modification), in full force and effect and the absence or existence (and the nature
thereof) of breaches or Events of Default hereunder and documents of consent to such Assignment
to such Lenders; and
(iv) Upon the receipt of a written request from Generator or any Lender,
Interconnection Company shall execute, or arrange for the delivery of, such certificates and other
documents (including a consent to assignment agreement on terms customary for project financed
transactions) as may be reasonably necessary in order for Generator to consummate the Financing.
(d) During the term of this Agreement, Interconnection Company shall not

consent of Generator, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed;
provided, however, that Generator’s consent shall not be required with respect to any amendment

Section 205 of the Federal Power Act or without receipt of any Governmental Approval required

Section 13.5 Waiver. Each Party may: (a) extend the time for the performance of any of

other term or condition of this Agreement. The failure of either Party to assert any of its rights or

Section 13.6 Validity and Severance. If any term, provision or condition of this
Agreement is held to be invalid, void or unenforceable by a Governmental Authority and such
holding is subject to no further appeal or judicial review, then such invalid, void, or unenforceable

terms, provisions and conditions of this Agreement shall continue in full force and effect. The
Parties shall endeavor in good faith to replace such invalid, void or unenforceable terms,
provisions or conditions with valid and enforceable terms, provisions or conditions which achieve
the purpose intended by the Parties to the greatest extent permitted by law.
Section 13.7 Governing Law. This Agreement shall be governed by, construed and
enforced in accordance with the laws of the State of Illinois, without giving effect to the choice
of law principles thereof.
Section 13.8 No Third Party Beneficiary. Except for the Lenders, the terms and
provisions of this Agreement are intended solely for the benefit of each Party and their respective
successors or permitted assigns, and it is not the intention of the Parties to confer third-party
beneficiary rights upon any other Person.
Section 13.9 Late or Nonpayment. Any amount not paid when due hereunder shall bear
interest from and including the applicable due date to but excluding the date such amount is paid,
at a rate equal to the lesser of: (a) the highest rate permitted under applicable Law; and (b) two
hundred (200) basis points per annum plus the rate per annum equal to the publicly announced
prime rate or reference rate for commercial loans to large businesses in effect from time to time
quoted by Citibank, N.A. as its “prime rate”; provided, that if a Citibank, N.A. prime rate is not
available, the applicable prime rate will be the announced prime rate or reference rate for
commercial loans in effect from time to time quoted by a bank with Ten Billion Dollars
($10,000,000,000) or more in assets in New York City, New York, selected by the Party to whom
interest is being paid.

perform its obligations under this Agreement, nor will any such delay or failure become a breach
or Event of Default under this Agreement, to the extent such delay or failure is caused by Force
Majeure, provided, that the affected Party: (a) provides prompt notice to the other Party after
becoming aware of the occurrence of such event of Force Majeure, describing the particulars of
the event of Force Majeure and giving an estimate of its expected duration and probable impact
on the performance of its obligations under this Agreement; (b) exercises commercially
reasonable efforts to continue to perform its obligations under this Agreement; (c) exercises
commercially reasonable efforts to correct or cure the event of Force Majeure so that the
suspension of performance is no greater in scope and no longer in duration than is dictated by the
event of Force Majeure; (d) exercises commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate or limit any
damages resulting from the event of Force Majeure; and (e) provides prompt notice to the other
Party of the cessation of the event of Force Majeure.
Section 13.11Time is of the Essence. Time is of the essence with respect to each and
every provision of this Agreement.
